					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The MSX was the other machine I was thinking of, and I had been playing around with its graphical limitations in the past with some degree of success. I don't know though, it's awfully close to just being the NES all over again; the Spectrum's different-ness is what drew me to it in the first place; the simplistic nature of the hardware and the machine's capabilities make it seem like it'd be fun to play with, without much pressure to make things look and sound amazing since you don't have much to work with (until the 128k, which got an AY3 PSG).</div>

