						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Drag wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It was a fun exercise, and I did it because I wanted to eventually test out if these &quot;1bpp&quot; graphics would compress better than the same graphics done in proper 2bpp, but I never got that far.</div><br />I guess that'd ultimately depend on the compression algorithm, but to me it does look like in many cases the color bytes would remain the same for multiple scanlines, more often than the pattern would remain the same. But don't forget the fact that MSX graphics don't need attributes and palettes, while the 2bpp graphics do, so you have to take that extra data into account.</div>

